There's a lot more to me and my crazy mind than just this 5 minute video, but here's a start. If you care to know me, more than just my music, or dog, and have followed my journey, you'll be hearing a lot more from me in the near future. I lost myself for a while, or maybe I was so distracted the past 20 years "succeeding" and celebrating that, I never really found myself. Been trying lately though, and with my head clear of drugs and alcohol and a little more sleep under my belt I'm getting happy fast. I am a bright burning light when I'm sober and happy and it's so contagious everyone and everything around me gravitated to me with a heavy pull. All that has been too much for me to accept and understand and connect with at times, so I've self sabotage and disconnected with as much drugs and vacations and mountains you make it I could distract myself with. But, now I have a little girl coming. I plan on being amazing Again as intended. For myself and for her. For my family. I can't drink and do drugs. I've abused them to no end since I was 14. I don't have a off button. So, being sober and shining bright is what I'll be instead. Our biggest fear is that we are great beyond measure. here's a bit about me and where I've been. I have a lot more to share. Stay tuned. Or go away. Either way, I have no room for negativity. It's light work. much love. Let's go! #mentalhealth

Mental health, suicide, why I don't really do original music anymore or like it's scene. I always should have done country I was told. I have a lot of hate for the fake and good marketing in music and I picked it as a career. I need to work on that.  I saw everyone and everything as a threat. Brought up that way. In every room. I thought I was the superior one like look at these fawns out here weak unaware of all these threats. In hindsight those people that grew up with a solid family foundation and trust and love we're lucky. I need to focus on me. They being said. You people (society) are allowing pollution to move across the waves. Music with no substance and people with no history of struggle in their life sell mental health and push music to monetize. It's not real nourishment and I'm struggling with seeing all the fake and ugly in the world. Being sincere transparent and authentic is all I know. Here's to another day sober strong and moving along.

I've  judged myself based off my inadequacies instead of my strengths. Over the years, there have been many things that I really wanted to know, or learn, or get better at, but I wouldn't humble myself enough to ask the question or ask for help because of the fear of how other men my piers would perceive me, because I think like most men, maybe women too, we or I, Have this ego that says we should be able to do this, and It can feel like the world is looking at me, thinking he should be able to do this, we should build things, we should fix things, we should repair things, we should get things running right, we should win all the fights,  we should know how to do everything and that's just not the case and so I've stopped myself from doing new things and stayed in my comfort zone, and I do really good at that, but if you only do really good at one thing for a long time, but Know and learn very little about a lot of other things, you can start to build some insecurities and you're building those insecurities in you, because you're not completing new goals and accomplishing new things, so how can you get the confidence? How can you feel like you can do it all?  it's a slippery slope to go down and for myself I intend to change that. For years a lot of people looked to me like I had it all together and so that's the role I played and I didn't know everything even when I acted like I did and now here I am with things I don't know, that's OK because there's plenty of room to grow,  so here I go.  I highly suggested if there's something you want to do or learn you ask and you try to do and learn and you do the best you can , that's what I'm going to do as a dad and that's what I'm going to do as a man and that's what I'm going to do is me, Dan. And also here's a picture of Dylan. 

Have a beautiful day guys!!! #men #man #dad #love she deserves my best.

"When I look in the mirror, I see perfection in the work, constant correction is the path that most hurts, but it's the one that best serves, it's funny sometimes, my selection of worth, my confession, is that my complexions been hurt, you can see on my face, but that's ok it's my fate, my reflections the result of all my fears to go be great, but it's ok too because i know got more days. the scars are supposed to hurt, they're here to teach or so I've learned,  thats the beauty of it, with the warmth of the fire, comes a risk you'll get burnt, But I won't stop playing until my Bodys in to the dirt, always singing my song for the people of the earth. My profession is to sing the lessons that i'm given, it's when i'm most alive, and the musics so forgiving my protection had me hungry for affection, but wouldn't let it in,  pushing all forms of connection, away with my aggression, but my progression has led me here, so love appears and as I stand outside of fear, letting all things pass. Problems seem to disappear, none of them last. so I'm gonna sit inside this moment, gonna savor savor, gonna hold it, gonna just be here, and I'd love to have you here with me, I'll show you love is always near."

The law of attraction, good vibrations: 

Have you ever spent time wondering how some people can continually attract negative situations into their life's, while others seem to attract nothing but beautiful situations into theirs. The concept behind this law of attraction contains power, possibility, and promise if you'll use it. You are a living, breathing, creative magnet. You have the ability to control what you attract into your life. Why not make a conscious decision to attract into your life all of the good you desire. historically there have always been small select groups of individuals who are aware of how to work at Harmony with this natural law of the universe, The law of attraction. This law clearly states that you can only attract to you that which is in harmony with you. Everything in this universe vibrates. Including your mind and body.  Look at your body through a microscope. It is a massive energy. Moving, vibrating. your mind controls the vibration you are in at any given moment you control your mind by the thoughts you choose no one can cause you to think something you don't want to think. This is where freedom comes in. This is also where the problem begins with most people, they permit what's happening around them to how they think. 90% of the population wish positive but think negative their negative thoughts put them in a negative vibration which by law determines what is attracted into their lives. as a creative individual you will continually attract good things into your life by thinking, positive thoughts and expecting the best life has to offer, you deserve it. science is a way of thinking more than it is a body of knowledge. man alone has the power to transform his thoughts into physical reality. Man alone can dream and make his dreams come true.

I've learned and grown from life's lessons a ton over the past 10 years. Most of which I've chose to do publicly, as for one I don't know what I'm doing on here or how to be a public figure, if that's whart you'd call being a musician , nor do I think that is necessary for me to do anymore. I've chosen to be so outspoken on everything because I've just been learning to do this whole life thing on the fly and that's what worked to get me here. My way may not of been yours and that doesn't make it wrong or right. I will say I'm definitely where I always wanted to be. In these past months especially I've learned less friends is better, most aren't on your team anyway and have thoughts about you you never knew about. Another is that the less alcohol and drugs that are in my life the better. Focusing all my new positive energy on my family, home and music. I'm rewarded everyday and I keep waking up happier and more powerful than ever. I don't have any advice or suggestions for you. I know that's a first right. I don't know much. But I'm rooting for you all. Liking the way things have turned out for me. I did this and I'm so stoked to see what I'll do next. Being more intentional with my time and inviting in much less energy. I used to take on so many new friends and ideas because I thought these people must be gravitating towards me for a reason and maybe if I allow them In we can help each other be happy, instead these people will suck the life out of you. I kept up with that energy for a long time.  I don't know how lol probably all the uppers. My body was always running hot and in those scenarios you usually crash. Im too strong for that. Im no victim of anything. I never have been my whole life, the few times it's happened have been my saddest moments. Get out of your own way. The victim woe is me mentality sucks and even the few times I fell in to it, I hated my self. That's a sad life. Not going that direction again. When in doubt get up and do something about it. Im in the process of writing a beautiful story. Enjoying the process and wishing you all health wealth and happiness. 🤙🏻🙏🏻❤️✅ #love #happy #healthy

Been spending a lot of time in these past months just reflecting. Who I am, who I've been, and who I want to be. Learning to accept change and respond to things from a more balanced place or not at all. Not every feeling I've ever had is valid and needs to be shared. Working through my own emotions instead of working out of emotion. Many times in my life I worked out off emotions. Ive been reactive. I see that as irresponsible now. I've always been a person that doesn't play the pretend well. If I'm mad you know it, if I'm sad you know it, if I'm happy and etc. if I don't like your energy you'll know it, I won't sit next to you and pretend all is good. I'll distance myself or ask you to leave. It seems with each new day I'm getting stronger and becoming a me a like better. This me doesn't have many friends. This me is centered and if you see this person move, it's with intention. It's been thought out. I won't claim to have it all figured out. I'm taking this journey day by day. Sometimes I float on my back in the lake under the burning sun and just allow all the things I don't want or I've grown through wash away from me. I get out of that lake grateful and lighter. Weightless on the water relaxing, breathing and smiling at the beauty my life is. Wishing you all a light day. One not so heavy with pressure and pain and guilt, but one where you float on loves wings with the sun on your face. Love you all. ✌🏻❤️ #love #grace #gratitude #happy #lakelife

After resisting gods love my whole life, self proclaiming, I didn't need anybody's love, his, my parents or anyone's, I sat in my truck today in the gym parking lot before going in, listening to 93.1 Christian Chanel and accepted god fully In to my heart. The sky was the brightest blue and the sun was shining strong. I cried a lot, I smiled a lot too. I felt a peace I'm not to familiar with. How wrong I was, and have always been. How hard I've tried my whole life to do this all on my own. Yes, I succeeded financially and socially, and in most things but still felt empty broken and without a peace.. I had everything I dreamed of, money, my dream girl, lake house, baby girl, and still felt alone and broken to bits. I need to be the best man I can be for Dylan and Megan. I need to feel whole, so I can give her a whole love. I'm going to tread lightly and hold my head up. One day at a time. I'm sharing this because I'm finally not embarrassed to say I want to know him and that I love him and I want him to know I'm proud. Letting god in my heart today isn't going to fix everything, I won't be using him as a crutch as I'm accountable for my actions. I will say, if anyone is out there struggling as I have been my whole life. Abandoned, unloved and alone and broken. Inviting god in to your heart is an option. For me, I feel lighter today. I feel like I'm not alone anymore. I pray for peace for all of you. I did everything but let god love me, my whole life, spiritually, drugs and alcohol, and everything In between, yet still never felt loved or whole. I'm gonna give some of it to god and see where things go. I love you all. Thanks for always being so good to me. I needed it. If you need me, I hope I can be a tool for you one day. Much love and enjoy your day. I would appreciate it if you'd all just allow me to express myself without this being an invitation for you to push your religions views or churches on me as I believe this whole thing is a church and I still don't trust religion. I'm hoping this might take the pain and weight off of one more persons heart today as it did mine. Thank you 🙏🏻❤️ I'm not asking you to love god or even believe. Just know I do. #god

Another disciplined morning. I'm feeling stronger than ever this week. Not just physically, but my heart, my mind and my soul. More than anything, I've never felt more connected, nor have I ever had such strong Meaning and purpose. More then any of my achievements, I think what I'm most happy about is that my beautiful daughter is going to get the most healed, strongest, worked on version of me. It's taken me a long time and in that time I've done a lot of work. I've entered in to the greatest chapter of my life, and I've got god with me for this part. I'm releasing two new songs soon. I hope you'll like them. I've cried, I've smiled, I've laughed and I've gotten angry. I did all this so vulnerabley because that's how I'm built. I have that capacity. Some of you sit in offices. I wrote this song right after we had Dylan. We decided right away that now that we made a baby, we wanted to get married and all share the last name. I wrote this song for her in our room, and then asked her to come in to the bedroom so I could play it for her. We already knew we were getting married from the delivery room and I know she didn't want to make a movie out of our proposal, as it's just not our style, so I knew the answer was yes already but felt the urge to sing it to her. Since then I've been performing it out live; and the response has been great. I'm told it's a hit and multiple people have asked after the performance "who wrote that" "I want that to be our wedding song" I guess I have a skill for that as many people used my song "I do" as their wedding songs already. It's easy to write love songs for me as I've been in love with the same girl near 20 years.  So excited to get it recorded and out to the masses. I'm told it's a hit!. But We shall see. Much love guys. Thanks for listening. My good friend gave a great compliment the other night and said, "you've personalized it so much and at the same time generalized it so everyone can feel it" made me happy. I want my songs to make people smile. Glad this one does that. #dantillerymusic #lovesongs #willyoumarryme #love #music #artist #detroit

Here's the things that fell to the waste side these past 10 months, due to having a baby. 

Daily ice baths, daily breath work/meditation/manifesting, sleep, a positive mindset. 

External problems came and went, as they do, but the difference was my capacity to handle them with love and light and gratitude, a full tank, I was running on empty both physically and spiritually, I mean, my heart was full, Dylan is my world and she makes me smile every second I see her, but when these eternal practices fall away, you're sleep deprived and a lot of external problems come your way, it can beat you down if you let it. I did for a minute. I got trapped in a negative feedback loop, it's happened before, I may happen again. I didn't like that me. I never do. Being at your best is the best. But it takes work. A lot of discipline and work. Keeping these practices up is going to have its challenges but all things worth having do. I look forward to jumping back in to all the things that make me my best , and ridding the things that keep me from it. Back to work. #doingthework #love #mastery
